rpt from.&#10;@param integer $count Maximum number of characters to take.&#10;@param string $more Optional. What to append if $str needs to be trimmed. Defaults to empty string.&#10;@return string The excerpt." ilk="function" line="3465" lineend="3475" name="wp_html_excerpt" returns="string" signature="string wp_html_excerpt(string $str, integer $count, string $more = null)"><variable citdl="string" ilk="argument" line="3465" name="str" /><variable citdl="integer" ilk="argument" line="3465" name="count" /><variable citdl="string" default="null" ilk="argument" line="3465" name="more" /><variable citdl="mb_substr()" line="3469" name="excerpt" /></scope><scope doc="Add a Base url to relative links in passed content.&#10;&#10;By default it supports the 'src' and 'href' attributes. However this can be&#10;changed via the 3rd param.&#10;&#10;@since 2.7.0&#10;&#10;@param string $content String to search for links in.&#10;@param string $base The base URL to prefix to links.&#10;@param array $attrs The attributes which should be processed.&#10;@return string The processed content." ilk="function" line="3490" lineend="3495" name="links_add_base_url" returns="string" signature="string links_add_base_url(string $content, string $base, array $attrs = array('src','href'))"><variable citdl="string" ilk="argument" line="3490" name="content" /><variable citdl="string" ilk="argument" line="3490" name="base" /><variable citdl="array" default="array('src','href')" ilk="argument" line="3490" name="attrs" /><variable attributes="__not_yet_defined__" citdl="base" line="3491" name="_links_add_base" /></scope><scope doc="Callback to add a base url to relative links in passed content.&#10;&#10;@since 2.7.0&#10;@access private&#10;&#10;@param string $m The matched link.&#10;@return string The processed link." ilk="function" line="3506" lineend="3514" name="_links_add_base" returns="string" signature="string _links_add_base(string $m)"><variable citdl="string" ilk="argument" line="3506" name="m" /><variable attributes="__not_yet_defined__" line="3507" name="_links_add_base" /></scope><scope doc="Adds a Target attribute to all links in passed content.&#10;&#10;This function by default only applies to &lt;a&gt; tags, however this can be&#10;modified by the 3rd param.&#10;&#10;&lt;b&gt;NOTE:&lt;/b&gt; Any current target attributed will be stripped and replaced.&#10;&#10;@since 2.7.0&#10;&#10;@param string $content String to search for links in.&#10;@param string $target The Target to add to the links.&#10;@param array $tags An array of tags to apply to.&#10;@return string The processed content." ilk="function" line="3531" lineend="3536" name="links_add_target" returns="string" signature="string links_add_target(string $content, string $target = '_blank', array $tags = array('a'))"><variable citdl="string" ilk="argument" line="3531" name="content" /><variable citdl="string" default="'_blank'" ilk="argument" line="3531" name="target" /><variable citdl="array" default="array('a')" ilk="argument" line="3531" name="tags" /><variable attributes="__not_yet_defined__" citdl="target" line="3532" name="_links_add_target" /></scope><scope doc="Callback to add a target attribute to all links in passed content.&#10;&#10;@since 2.7.0&#10;@access private&#10;&#10;@param string $m The matched link.&#10;@return string The processed link." ilk="function" line="3547" lineend="3552" name="_links_add_target" returns="string" signature="string _links_add_target(string $m)"><variable citdl="string" ilk="argument" line="3547" name="m" /><variable citdl="m" line="3549" name="tag" /><variable citdl="preg_replace()" line="3550" name="link" /><variable attributes="__not_yet_defined__" line="3548" name="_links_add_target" /></scope><scope doc="Normalize EOL characters and strip duplicate whitespace.&#10;&#10;@since 2.7.0&#10;&#10;@param string $str The string to normalize.&#10;@return string The normalized string." ilk="function" line="3562" lineend="3567" name="normalize_whitespace" r